**Segments**

The contextual advertising market can be segmented based on various factors to understand the industry landscape better. One way to categorize the market is by **type**, which includes **In-Text Ads, In-Image Ads, In-Video Ads, In-Frame Ads, and Others**. Each of these types serves a specific purpose and targets audiences through different mediums within online content. Another segmentation approach is based on **platform**, which includes **Desktop and Mobile**. With the increasing use of mobile devices, advertisers are focusing more on mobile platforms to reach consumers effectively. Furthermore, the market can also be segmented by **industry vertical**, such as **Retail, Healthcare, Media & Entertainment, BFSI, and Others**. Understanding the industry verticals helps in tailoring contextual advertising strategies to suit the specific needs and preferences of different sectors.

